Sed finis· . . . loqui possum] Quoted by Quintilian (xi. 3. 173): “ Illa quoque mire facit in peroratione velut deficientis dolore et fatigatione confessio : ut pro eodem Milone, ·Sed finis . . . possum :’ quae simi- lem verbis habere debent etiam pronun- tiationem.'' The whole of this third chap- ter of Quintilian is worth reading. lt shows how much more there was in Roman ora- tory than in the frigid talk of our men who are called speakers. As to ‘pronuntiatim’ says Quintilian, “a plerisque actio dicitur, sed prius nomen a voce, sequens a gestu videtur accipere. Namque. notionem Cicero alias quasi sermonem, alius eloquentiam quandam corporis dicit. Idem tamen duas ejus partes facit, quae sunt eaedem pronun- tiationis. vocem atquc motum.
